courses.course_syllabus:
This course covers the fundamental concepts of design process of medical device and preparation of business proposal. Students have to form groups to produce a medical device and prepare a business proposal. Written reports, presentations, and/or business/operation plan are required. Students should have acquired basic engineering design skills and practical skills that are directly transferable to further innovation work in their future careers.
To exemplify students’learnt abilities in problem-solving and in designing new medical devices, based on project-based learning practices, students are required to form groups to complete the following tasks as a group project:
- Define a problem/goal (in relation to medical or healthcare devices) provided or approved by course instructor;
- Understand the problem/goal, including the related complexities, uncertain parameters, and practical constraints, etc.;
- Conduct market search;
- Discuss and analyze findings;
- Develop and implement a detailed plan;
- Present the prototype in class;
- Receive and evaluate feedbacks provided by instructors and clinical professionals; and
- Write up a business proposal.

